rComments: I just finished my third year taking her HIS220 class and I absolutely loved it. I don't think I loved the course so much as professor Lindeman though because she is very easy to understand unlike many other profs. Her lectures follow a specific theme which makes it easy to follow along and she is super super friendly.

Lindeman's lectures are tough and I would recommend recording them as I barely had breaks in my typing. She definitely knows a ton about history and gender. She works hard and thus expects you to work really hard, read primary sources, and analyse well. Also, if you attend her classes, be prepared to read or be publicly shamed.
